{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":516,"text":"I'm going to tell you about an affliction I suffer from."},{"time":4623,"text":"And I have a funny feeling that quite a few of you"},{"time":7127,"text":"suffer from it as well."},{"time":9047,"text":"When I'm walking around an art gallery,"},{"time":11144,"text":"rooms and rooms full of paintings,"},{"time":13247,"text":"after about 15 or 20 minutes,"},{"time":17764,"text":"I realize I'm not thinking about the paintings."},{"time":19655,"text":"I'm not connecting to them."},{"time":21263,"text":"Instead, I'm thinking about that cup of coffee"},{"time":23767,"text":"I desperately need to wake me up."},{"time":26767,"text":"I'm suffering from gallery fatigue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29951,"text":"How many of you out there suffer from --"},{"time":32327,"text":"yes. Ha ha, ha ha!"},{"time":34332,"text":"Now, sometimes you might last longer"},{"time":36482,"text":"than 20 minutes, or even shorter,"},{"time":38576,"text":"but I think we all suffer from it. And do you have"},{"time":40790,"text":"the accompanying guilt?"},{"time":42871,"text":"For me, I look at the paintings on the wall"},{"time":45858,"text":"and I think, somebody has decided to put them there,"},{"time":48873,"text":"thinks they're good enough to be on that wall,"},{"time":51401,"text":"but I don't always see it."},{"time":52759,"text":"In fact, most of the time I don't see it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55423,"text":"And I leave feeling actually unhappy."},{"time":59197,"text":"I feel guilty and unhappy with myself,"},{"time":62664,"text":"rather than thinking there's something wrong with the painting,"},{"time":64727,"text":"I think there's something wrong with me."},{"time":66184,"text":"And that's not a good experience, to leave a gallery like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69092,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":70363,"text":"The thing is, I think we should give ourselves a break."},{"time":72672,"text":"If you think about going into a restaurant,"},{"time":75132,"text":"when you look at the menu, are you expected to order"},{"time":78819,"text":"every single thing on the menu?"},{"time":81002,"text":"No! You select."},{"time":82884,"text":"If you go into a department store to buy a shirt,"},{"time":86059,"text":"are you going to try on every single shirt"},{"time":89036,"text":"and want every single shirt?"},{"time":90364,"text":"Of course not, you can be selective. It's expected."},{"time":94491,"text":"How come, then, it's not so expected"},{"time":97112,"text":"to be selective when we go to an art gallery?"},{"time":99685,"text":"Why are we supposed to have a connection with every single painting?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":102980,"text":"Well I'm trying to take a different approach."},{"time":105684,"text":"And there's two things I do:"},{"time":107302,"text":"When I go into a gallery, first of all, I go quite fast,"},{"time":111796,"text":"and I look at everything, and I pinpoint the ones"},{"time":116031,"text":"that make me slow down for some reason or other."},{"time":119085,"text":"I don't even know why they make me slow down, but something"},{"time":121886,"text":"pulls me like a magnet"},{"time":123943,"text":"and then I ignore all the others, and I just go to that painting."},{"time":127061,"text":"So it's the first thing I do is, I do my own curation."},{"time":129525,"text":"I choose a painting. It might just be one painting in 50."},{"time":132821,"text":"And then the second thing I do is I stand in front of that painting,"},{"time":136511,"text":"and I tell myself a story about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139588,"text":"Why a story? Well, I think that we are wired,"},{"time":143186,"text":"our DNA tells us to tell stories."},{"time":147077,"text":"We tell stories all the time about everything,"},{"time":149446,"text":"and I think we do it because the world is kind of a crazy, chaotic place,"},{"time":154557,"text":"and sometimes stories, we're trying to make sense of the world a little bit,"},{"time":158508,"text":"trying to bring some order to it."},{"time":160677,"text":"Why not apply that to our looking at paintings?"},{"time":164668,"text":"So I now have this sort of restaurant menu"},{"time":168383,"text":"visiting of art galleries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171606,"text":"There are three paintings I'm going to show you now"},{"time":174814,"text":"that are paintings that made me stop in my tracks"},{"time":177878,"text":"and want to tell stories about them."},{"time":180424,"text":"The first one needs little introduction --"},{"time":183975,"text":"\"Girl with a Pearl Earring\" by Johannes Vermeer,"},{"time":187006,"text":"17th-century Dutch painter."},{"time":189162,"text":"This is the most glorious painting."},{"time":191662,"text":"I first saw it when I was 19,"},{"time":193806,"text":"and I immediately went out and got a poster of it,"},{"time":196086,"text":"and in fact I still have that poster. 30 years later it's hanging in my house."},{"time":200243,"text":"It's accompanied me everywhere I've gone,"},{"time":203393,"text":"I never tire of looking at her."}]},{"cues":[{"time":205737,"text":"What made me stop in my tracks about her to begin with"},{"time":209516,"text":"was just the gorgeous colors he uses"},{"time":212073,"text":"and the light falling on her face."},{"time":214017,"text":"But I think what's kept me still coming back"},{"time":216801,"text":"year after year is another thing, and that is"},{"time":219857,"text":"the look on her face, the conflicted look on her face."},{"time":223551,"text":"I can't tell if she's happy or sad,"},{"time":225969,"text":"and I change my mind all the time."},{"time":228936,"text":"So that keeps me coming back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232535,"text":"One day, 16 years after I had this poster on my wall,"},{"time":236544,"text":"I lay in bed and looked at her,"},{"time":239226,"text":"and I suddenly thought, I wonder what"},{"time":241805,"text":"the painter did to her to make her look like that."},{"time":245723,"text":"And it was the first time I'd ever thought that"},{"time":248667,"text":"the expression on her face is actually reflecting"},{"time":251467,"text":"how she feels about him."},{"time":253606,"text":"Always before I'd thought of it as a portrait of a girl."},{"time":256762,"text":"Now I began to think of it as a portrait of a relationship."},{"time":261531,"text":"And I thought, well, what is that relationship?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":264363,"text":"So I went to find out. I did some research and discovered,"},{"time":267571,"text":"we have no idea who she is."},{"time":269896,"text":"In fact, we don't know who any of the models"},{"time":272243,"text":"in any of Vermeer's paintings are,"},{"time":274603,"text":"and we know very little about Vermeer himself."},{"time":276730,"text":"Which made me go, \"Yippee!\""},{"time":279504,"text":"I can do whatever I want, I can come up with whatever story I want to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284163,"text":"So here's how I came up with the story."},{"time":286759,"text":"First of all, I thought,"},{"time":288636,"text":"I've got to get her into the house."},{"time":290728,"text":"How does Vermeer know her?"},{"time":293216,"text":"Well, there've been suggestions that"},{"time":294760,"text":"she is his 12-year-old daughter."},{"time":299183,"text":"The daughter at the time was 12 when he painted the painting."},{"time":301408,"text":"And I thought, no, it's a very intimate look,"},{"time":304104,"text":"but it's not a look a daughter gives her father."},{"time":306288,"text":"For one thing, in Dutch painting of the time,"},{"time":308128,"text":"if a woman's mouth was open, it was indicating sexual availability."},{"time":311720,"text":"It would have been inappropriate for Vermeer"},{"time":313608,"text":"to paint his daughter like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":315504,"text":"So it's not his daughter, but it's somebody"},{"time":317384,"text":"close to him, physically close to him."},{"time":319634,"text":"Well, who else would be in the house?"},{"time":321898,"text":"A servant, a lovely servant."},{"time":325281,"text":"So, she's in the house."},{"time":326842,"text":"How do we get her into the studio?"},{"time":329503,"text":"We don't know very much about Vermeer,"},{"time":331637,"text":"but the little bits that we do know, one thing we know"},{"time":333776,"text":"is that he married a Catholic woman, they lived with her mother"},{"time":336767,"text":"in a house where he had his own room"},{"time":339040,"text":"where he -- his studio. He also had 11 children."},{"time":343323,"text":"It would have been a chaotic, noisy household."},{"time":346400,"text":"And if you've seen Vermeer's paintings before,"},{"time":349344,"text":"you know that they're incredibly calm and quiet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":353208,"text":"How does a painter paint such calm, quiet paintings with 11 kids around?"},{"time":357104,"text":"Well, he compartmentalizes his life."},{"time":359400,"text":"He gets to his studio, and he says, \"Nobody comes in here."},{"time":363080,"text":"Not the wife, not the kids. Okay, the maid can come in and clean.\""},{"time":367808,"text":"She's in the studio. He's got her in the studio, they're together."},{"time":374859,"text":"And he decides to paint her."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376939,"text":"He has her wear very plain clothes."},{"time":379207,"text":"Now, all of the women, or most of the women in Vermeer's other paintings"},{"time":382578,"text":"wore velvet, silk, fur, very sumptuous materials."},{"time":388544,"text":"This is very plain; the only thing that isn't plain"},{"time":391064,"text":"is her pearl earring."},{"time":393104,"text":"Now, if she's a servant, there is no way she could afford"},{"time":396551,"text":"a pair of pearl earrings."},{"time":398758,"text":"So those are not her pearl earrings. Whose are they?"},{"time":402020,"text":"We happen to know, there's a list of Catharina, the wife's clothes."},{"time":407061,"text":"Amongst them a yellow coat with white fur,"},{"time":410677,"text":"a yellow and black bodice,"},{"time":412424,"text":"and you see these clothes on lots of other paintings,"},{"time":416118,"text":"different women in the paintings, Vermeer's paintings."},{"time":419232,"text":"So clearly, her clothes were lent to various different women."},{"time":423710,"text":"It's not such a leap of faith to take"},{"time":426229,"text":"that that pearl earring actually belongs to his wife."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429813,"text":"So we've got all the elements for our story."},{"time":432990,"text":"She's in the studio with him for a long time."},{"time":435420,"text":"These paintings took a long time to make."},{"time":437463,"text":"They would have spent the time alone, all that time."},{"time":440334,"text":"She's wearing his wife's pearl earring."},{"time":442334,"text":"She's gorgeous. She obviously loves him. She's conflicted."},{"time":445149,"text":"And does the wife know? Maybe not."},{"time":447941,"text":"And if she doesn't, well --"},{"time":451319,"text":"that's the story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":453174,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":455351,"text":"The next painting I'm going to talk about"},{"time":457941,"text":"is called \"Boy Building a House of Cards\" by Chardin."},{"time":461188,"text":"He's an 18th-century French painter best known for his still lifes,"},{"time":465564,"text":"but he did occasionally paint people."},{"time":468157,"text":"And in fact, he painted four versions of this painting,"},{"time":472124,"text":"different boys building houses of cards, all concentrated."},{"time":476084,"text":"I like this version the best, because some of the boys"},{"time":479548,"text":"are older and some are younger, and to me, this one,"},{"time":482941,"text":"like Goldilocks's porridge, is just right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":485893,"text":"He's not quite a child, and he's not quite a man."},{"time":489884,"text":"He's absolutely balanced between innocence and experience,"},{"time":494677,"text":"and that made me stop in my tracks in front of this painting."},{"time":499160,"text":"And I looked at his face. It's like a Vermeer painting a bit."},{"time":502877,"text":"The light comes in from the left, his face is bathed"},{"time":505500,"text":"in this glowing light. It's right in the center of the painting,"},{"time":507724,"text":"and you look at it, and I found that when I was looking at it,"},{"time":510736,"text":"I was standing there going,"},{"time":511943,"text":"\"Look at me. Please look at me.\""},{"time":514896,"text":"And he didn't look at me. He was still looking at his cards,"},{"time":517632,"text":"and that's one of the seductive elements of this painting is,"},{"time":520384,"text":"he's so focused on what he's doing that he doesn't look at us."},{"time":524874,"text":"And that is, to me, the sign of a masterpiece,"},{"time":528767,"text":"of a painting when there's a lack of resolution."},{"time":532744,"text":"He's never going to look at me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":534265,"text":"So I was thinking of a story where,"},{"time":535944,"text":"if I'm in this position, who could be there looking at him?"},{"time":539160,"text":"Not the painter, I don't want to think about the painter."},{"time":541362,"text":"I'm thinking of an older version of himself."},{"time":543888,"text":"He's a man, a servant, an older servant looking at this younger servant,"},{"time":549833,"text":"saying, \"Look at me. I want to warn you about"},{"time":552304,"text":"what you're about to go through. Please look at me.\""},{"time":554754,"text":"And he never does."}]},{"cues":[{"time":556280,"text":"And that lack of resolution, the lack of resolution in \"Girl with a Pearl Earring\" --"},{"time":560083,"text":"we don't know if she's happy or sad."},{"time":562127,"text":"I've written an entire novel about her,"},{"time":563776,"text":"and I still don't know if she's happy or sad."},{"time":565776,"text":"Again and again, back to the painting,"},{"time":567880,"text":"looking for the answer, looking for the story to fill in that gap."},{"time":572561,"text":"And we may make a story, and it satisfies us momentarily,"},{"time":576008,"text":"but not really, and we come back again and again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581823,"text":"The last painting I'm going to talk about"},{"time":584361,"text":"is called \"Anonymous\" by anonymous. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":589225,"text":"This is a Tudor portrait bought by the National Portrait Gallery."},{"time":592276,"text":"They thought it was a man named Sir Thomas Overbury,"},{"time":594889,"text":"and then they discovered that it wasn't him,"},{"time":597553,"text":"and they have no idea who it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":599153,"text":"Now, in the National Portrait Gallery,"},{"time":601296,"text":"if you don't know the biography of the painting,"},{"time":603065,"text":"it's kind of useless to you."},{"time":604689,"text":"They can't hang it on the wall, because they don't know who he is."},{"time":607113,"text":"So unfortunately, this orphan spends most of his time in storage,"},{"time":612017,"text":"along with quite a number of other orphans,"},{"time":614161,"text":"some of them some beautiful paintings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616672,"text":"This painting made me stop in my tracks for three reasons:"},{"time":621675,"text":"One is the disconnection between his mouth"},{"time":624552,"text":"that's smiling and his eyes that are wistful."},{"time":627257,"text":"He's not happy, and why isn't he happy?"},{"time":630264,"text":"The second thing that really attracted me"},{"time":633981,"text":"were his bright red cheeks."},{"time":635697,"text":"He is blushing. He's blushing for his portrait being made!"},{"time":639304,"text":"This must be a guy who blushes all the time."},{"time":642338,"text":"What is he thinking about that's making him blush?"},{"time":644480,"text":"The third thing that made me stop in my tracks"},{"time":648256,"text":"is his absolutely gorgeous doublet."},{"time":651056,"text":"Silk, gray, those beautiful buttons."},{"time":654624,"text":"And you know what it makes me think of,"},{"time":656256,"text":"is it's sort of snug and puffy; it's like a duvet spread over a bed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":661048,"text":"I kept thinking of beds and red cheeks,"},{"time":663704,"text":"and of course I kept thinking of sex when I looked at him,"},{"time":666464,"text":"and I thought, is that what he's thinking about?"},{"time":669072,"text":"And I thought, if I'm going to make a story,"},{"time":671344,"text":"what's the last thing I'm going to put in there?"},{"time":673328,"text":"Well, what would a Tudor gentleman be preoccupied with?"},{"time":676958,"text":"And I thought, well, Henry VIII, okay."},{"time":678888,"text":"He'd be preoccupied with his inheritance, with his heir."},{"time":683032,"text":"Who is going to inherit his name and his fortune?"},{"time":686681,"text":"You put all those together, and you've got your story"},{"time":690561,"text":"to fill in that gap that makes you keep coming back."},{"time":693915,"text":"Now, here's the story."},{"time":698636,"text":"It's short."}]},{"cues":[{"time":701566,"text":"\"Rosy\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":704297,"text":"I am still wearing the white brocade doublet Caroline gave me."},{"time":708347,"text":"It has a plain high collar, detachable sleeves"},{"time":712658,"text":"and intricate buttons of twisted silk thread,"},{"time":715834,"text":"set close together so that the fit is snug."},{"time":718760,"text":"The doublet makes me think of a coverlet on the vast bed."},{"time":722323,"text":"Perhaps that was the intention."},{"time":726073,"text":"I first wore it at an elaborate dinner her parents held in our honor."},{"time":730991,"text":"I knew even before I stood up to speak"},{"time":732817,"text":"that my cheeks were inflamed."},{"time":735386,"text":"I have always flushed easily, from physical exertion,"},{"time":739087,"text":"from wine, from high emotion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":741442,"text":"As a boy, I was teased by my sisters and by schoolboys,"},{"time":745907,"text":"but not by George."},{"time":748354,"text":"Only George could call me Rosy."},{"time":751428,"text":"I would not allow anyone else."},{"time":753587,"text":"He managed to make the word tender."},{"time":757811,"text":"When I made the announcement, George did not"},{"time":760610,"text":"turn rosy, but went pale as my doublet."},{"time":763674,"text":"He should not have been surprised."},{"time":765578,"text":"It has been a common assumption"},{"time":767250,"text":"that I would one day marry his cousin."},{"time":771098,"text":"But it is difficult to hear the words aloud."},{"time":773682,"text":"I know, I could barely utter them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":776983,"text":"Afterwards, I found George on the terrace overlooking the kitchen garden."},{"time":781385,"text":"Despite drinking steadily all afternoon, he was still pale."},{"time":786642,"text":"We stood together and watched the maids cut lettuces."},{"time":790867,"text":"\"What do you think of my doublet?\" I asked."}]},{"cues":[{"time":793129,"text":"He glanced at me. \"That collar looks to be strangling you.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":798573,"text":"\"We will still see each other,\" I insisted."},{"time":800577,"text":"\"We can still hunt and play cards and attend court."},{"time":803865,"text":"Nothing need change.\""},{"time":805601,"text":"George did not speak."},{"time":809318,"text":"\"I am 23 years old. It is time for me to marry"},{"time":812712,"text":"and produce an heir. It is expected of me.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":816817,"text":"George drained another glass of claret and turned to me."},{"time":820398,"text":"\"Congratulations on your upcoming nuptials, James."},{"time":824481,"text":"I'm sure you'll be content together.\""},{"time":829317,"text":"He never used my nickname again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":832634,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":834393,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":837775,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":838957,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}